      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it's a debate, but like, from a purely legal/scholarly perspective, which one actually holds more weight? if you look at the actual text and history, isn't the originalist argument pretty much the only one that has a solid basis in the document itself? the other side seems more like they're just making up rules based on modern vibes.",
