      "content": "The concern that evolving interpretations lead to legal instability is a core criticism leveled against judicial review. Originalists argue that without a stable, text-based anchor, the Constitution becomes entirely subjective, allowing personal ideology to dictate law. Those who support a flexible view argue that rigid adherence to 18th-century understandings would render the document obsolete and incapable of governing a modern republic. The tension between textual fidelity and functional necessity remains the central, unresolved debate in constitutional law.",
